Formula 1 - 2012 season - Round 19 - USA Grand Prix [BRAZILIAN BROADCAST]

With Sergio Mauricio, commentaries by Lito Cavalcanti.

And Globo TV strikes again! Brazilian National Football (soccer for americans) Championship is approaching its end, and because a major team is about to be demoted to the 2nd division championship, Globo TV preferred to show football instead of Formula 1 looking for audience. Bernie Ecclestone didn't like it. After negotiations, SporTV, a cable channel also from Globo Corporation, transmitted the race live, at 4:3 standard definition.

Globo will transmit the race at 11pm, brazilian time, which I'll also record.
